OL,6,FBut reports in The Guardian and The
OL,7,FDaily Telegraph suggested Business
OL,8,FSecretary Jonathan Reynolds was now
OL,9,Fconsidering a range of options
OL,10,Fincluding taking the company back into
OL,11,Fpublic ownership for the first time
OL,12,Fsince 1988.
OL,14,FA Government source told The Guardian
OL,15,Fthat renationalisation was "the least
OL,16,Fattractive option" due to its
OL,17,Fsignificant cost, but said it would be
OL,18,F"negligent not to look at it".
